name: Apple Inc.
description: Apple designs, manufactures, and markets smartphones, personal computers, tablets, wearables, and accessories. The company also sells digital content, apps, and services.

name: Microsoft Corp.
description: Microsoft develops and licenses consumer and enterprise software, including Windows, Office, Azure cloud services, and Xbox gaming.

name: Alphabet Inc.
description: Alphabet is the parent company of Google. It operates the world's largest search engine, YouTube, Android OS, and Google Cloud platform.

name: Amazon.com Inc.
description: Amazon is the world's largest e-commerce and cloud computing company. Its AWS division is the leading cloud infrastructure provider globally.

name: NVIDIA Corp.
description: NVIDIA designs GPUs and system-on-chip units. The company is the dominant supplier of AI training and inference accelerator hardware.

name: Meta Platforms
description: Meta Platforms operates Facebook, Instagram, WhatsApp, and Messenger. The company is also investing heavily in virtual reality and the metaverse.

name: Tesla Inc.
description: Tesla designs, manufactures, and sells electric vehicles, battery energy storage, and solar products. It is the world's most valuable automaker.

name: JPMorgan Chase
description: JPMorgan Chase is the largest bank in the United States by assets. It provides investment banking, financial services, and asset management.

name: Bank of America
description: Bank of America is one of the world's largest financial institutions, serving individual consumers, small businesses, and large corporations.

name: Goldman Sachs
description: Goldman Sachs is a leading global investment banking, securities, and investment management firm serving corporations, governments, and individuals.

name: Visa Inc.
description: Visa operates the world's largest electronic payments network, facilitating digital payments among consumers, merchants, and financial institutions.

name: Johnson & Johnson
description: Johnson & Johnson develops medical devices, pharmaceuticals, and consumer health products. It is one of the world's largest healthcare companies.

name: UnitedHealth Group
description: UnitedHealth Group is the largest healthcare company in the US, offering insurance plans through UnitedHealthcare and data analytics via Optum.

name: Pfizer Inc.
description: Pfizer discovers, develops, and manufactures healthcare products including medicines, vaccines, and consumer healthcare products worldwide.

name: AbbVie Inc.
description: AbbVie is a biopharmaceutical company focused on immunology, oncology, neuroscience, and eye care. Humira is its top-selling drug.

name: Merck & Co.
description: Merck is a global pharmaceutical company known for Keytruda, one of the world's best-selling cancer immunotherapy drugs.

name: Exxon Mobil
description: Exxon Mobil is the largest publicly traded oil and gas company. It explores, produces, and refines petroleum and natural gas worldwide.

name: Chevron Corp.
description: Chevron is an integrated energy company involved in oil and gas exploration, production, refining, and chemical manufacturing.

name: ConocoPhillips
description: ConocoPhillips is the world's largest independent exploration and production company, focused on conventional and unconventional oil and gas.

name: Coca-Cola Co.
description: Coca-Cola is the world's largest beverage company, manufacturing and distributing over 200 brands of non-alcoholic beverages globally.

name: PepsiCo Inc.
description: PepsiCo manufactures and distributes beverages and snack foods. Brands include Pepsi, Lay's, Gatorade, Quaker, and Doritos.

name: Procter & Gamble
description: Procter & Gamble is the world's largest consumer goods company. Brands include Tide, Pampers, Gillette, Oral-B, and Head & Shoulders.

name: Walmart Inc.
description: Walmart is the world's largest retailer by revenue, operating hypermarkets, discount department stores, and grocery stores in 24 countries.

name: Nike Inc.
description: Nike is the world's largest athletic footwear and apparel company. Its brands include Nike, Jordan, Converse, and Air Max.

name: McDonald's Corp.
description: McDonald's is the world's largest restaurant chain by revenue, with over 40,000 locations in more than 100 countries.

name: Caterpillar Inc.
description: Caterpillar is the world's largest manufacturer of construction and mining equipment, diesel and natural gas engines, and industrial turbines.

name: Boeing Co.
description: Boeing is the world's largest aerospace company, manufacturing commercial jetliners, defense aircraft, satellites, and space vehicles.

name: Honeywell Intl.
description: Honeywell produces aerospace products, building technologies, performance materials, and safety and productivity solutions.

name: United Parcel Service
description: UPS is the world's largest package delivery company, providing transportation, distribution, contract logistics, and financial services.

name: GE Aerospace
description: GE Aerospace is a global leader in jet engines and aviation systems, providing engines and services for commercial and military aircraft.

name: Alibaba Group
description: Alibaba is China's largest e-commerce company, operating Taobao, Tmall, and Alibaba Cloud. It also has interests in logistics, media, and fintech.

name: Taiwan Semiconductor
description: TSMC is the world's largest dedicated semiconductor foundry, manufacturing chips for Apple, NVIDIA, AMD, and other major technology companies.

name: Toyota Motor Corp.
description: Toyota is the world's largest automaker by volume, producing a range of vehicles from economy cars to luxury Lexus models and hydrogen fuel cell vehicles.

name: Novo Nordisk
description: Novo Nordisk is a global pharmaceutical company specializing in diabetes care. It manufactures Ozempic and Wegovy, leading GLP-1 weight loss drugs.

name: SAP SE
description: SAP is the world's largest enterprise software company by revenue, providing ERP, supply chain, HR, and business intelligence solutions.

name: Shopify Inc.
description: Shopify provides an e-commerce platform for merchants to create online stores, process payments, and manage inventory across multiple channels.

name: Vanguard Total Bond ETF
description: Vanguard Total Bond Market ETF tracks the Bloomberg US Aggregate Bond Index, providing broad exposure to US investment-grade bonds.

name: iShares 20+ Year Treasury
description: iShares 20+ Year Treasury Bond ETF tracks long-term US Treasury bonds. It is highly sensitive to interest rate changes.

name: iShares High Yield Corporate
description: iShares High Yield Corporate Bond ETF provides exposure to US dollar-denominated, high-yield corporate bonds with higher risk and return.

name: Vanguard Real Estate ETF
description: Vanguard Real Estate ETF tracks the MSCI US Investable Market Real Estate 25/50 Index, providing diversified exposure to US REITs.

name: Realty Income Corp.
description: Realty Income is a real estate investment trust that invests in freestanding commercial properties under long-term net lease agreements. It pays monthly dividends.
